&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-30"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;        pandoc -r rst -w gfm -o &lt;span class="nv"&gt;$@&lt;/span&gt; $&amp;lt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-31"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-32"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;%.gfm.html &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; %.&lt;span class="n"&gt;gfm&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-33"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;        pandoc -s -r gfm -w html -H fancy.style -o &lt;span class="nv"&gt;$@&lt;/span&gt; $&amp;lt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-34"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-35"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;.PHONY&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;clean&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-36"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-37"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;clean&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-38"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;        -rm *.html *.native os.version pandoc.version docutils.version *.gfm
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-39"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-40"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="nf"&gt;.depend&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="o"&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class="n"&gt;rnf&lt;/span&gt;-&lt;span class="n"&gt;issue&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class="n"&gt;rst&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-41"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;        rst-depends rnf-issue.rst &amp;gt;&lt;span class="nv"&gt;$@&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-42"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;
&lt;a name="rest_code_3a5c67a458534d7c84275773676d14eb-43"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span class="cp"&gt;include .depend&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;p&gt;This may seem complex, but in practice I use templates to start out
all the files and by building it all with &lt;span class="program"&gt;make&lt;/span&gt; and &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://pandoc.org"&gt;pandoc&lt;/a&gt;
using the &lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;include&lt;/code&gt; directive of &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://docutils.sourceforge.io/rst.html"&gt;reST&lt;/a&gt; I ensure that the contents of
the message are correctly built from the various included files.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>gfm</category><category>github flavored markdown</category><category>issues</category><category>pandoc</category><category>pandoc-discuss</category><category>restructuredtext</category><category>rst</category><guid>https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2020/08/05/how-i-author-e-mails-to-pandoc-discuss-and-issues-on-the-pandoc-repo/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 05 Aug 2020 18:40:53 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>